## EXCEPT (MySQL using NOT EXISTS)
### 31. Find current employees who are not former employees.

```sql
SELECT *
FROM CurrentEmployees c
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM FormerEmployees f
    WHERE c.EmployeeID = f.EmployeeID
);
```

### 32. Find former employees who are not current employees.

```sql
SELECT *
FROM FormerEmployees f
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM CurrentEmployees c
    WHERE f.EmployeeID = c.EmployeeID
);
```

### 33. Find domestic customers not present internationally.

```sql
SELECT *
FROM DomesticCustomers d
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM InternationalCustomers i
    WHERE d.CustomerID = i.CustomerID
);
```

### 34. Find online orders not present in store orders.

```sql
SELECT *
FROM OnlineOrders o
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM StoreOrders s
    WHERE o.OrderID = s.OrderID
);
```

### 35. Find departments that exist only in CurrentEmployees.

```sql
SELECT DISTINCT Department
FROM CurrentEmployees
WHERE Department NOT IN (
    SELECT Department
    FROM FormerEmployees
);
```

### 36. Find employee IDs existing only in CurrentEmployees.

```sql
SELECT EmployeeID
FROM CurrentEmployees c
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM FormerEmployees f
    WHERE c.EmployeeID = f.EmployeeID
);
```

### 37. Find employee IDs existing only in FormerEmployees.

```sql
SELECT EmployeeID
FROM FormerEmployees f
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM CurrentEmployees c
    WHERE f.EmployeeID = c.EmployeeID
